28/09/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- Police used tear gas Monday (September 27th) to disperse Greek truck owners who kicked off their third week of protests against government plans to liberalise their sector.
The truckers planned to block a road connecting Thessaloniki and Athens.
One person was arrested during the unrest.
The protestors say they will ignore a government order to return to their jobs.
(AP, ANA-MPA - 27/09/10)
